###########################
#  Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"answerHints.pl",

"PGML.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

###########################
#  Setup

Context("Numeric");
$t = random(3, 5);
$P = random(1000, 5000, 500);
$r = random(4, 8);
$rate = $r/100;
$I = $P*$r/100*$t;

$rhs = $rate*$t;


###########################
#  Main text

BEGIN_PGML
Find the principal invested if [`$[$I]`] interest was earned in [$t] years at an interest rate of [$r]%.

[_________________]{$P}

*Hint:  I = PRT*

END_PGML


############################
#  Solution

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
We can use the formula

*I = PRT*

to solve simple interest problems.

I = interest earned,
P = principal,
R = interest rate (as a decimal),
T = time (in years)

In this problem,

I = [$I]

P = ?

R = [$rate]

T = [$t]

If we plug those values into the formula, we get:

[`[$I] = x \cdot [$rate] \cdot [$t]`]

[`[$I] = [$rhs]x`]

[`x = [$I] \div [$rhs] = [$P]`]

[`$[$P]`] was invested.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

COMMENT('MathObject version. Uses PGML.');

ENDDOCUMENT();